## What This Module Does

VLorenzPlugin is a chaotic attractor module that generates continuously evolving X/Y/Z/T outputs using the Lorenz differential equations. It produces butterfly chaos patterns that never repeat, making it ideal for driving video parameters through constantly evolving trajectories. The module provides smooth, organic motion that can be used to modulate visual effects, camera movements, or any parameter requiring non-repetitive, natural-looking variation.

## What It Does NOT Do

- Does not generate visual output directly (uses dummy shader)
- Does not provide real-time parameter editing during playback
- Does not support multiple attractor types (only Lorenz)
- Does not include audio reactivity
- Does not provide 3D visualization of the attractor itself

